No laundry, which would be helpful for those traveling for a long time.The location is in the heart of Seattle.	It's in the heart of the downtown from which you can walk to Seattle Center or Pike Place Market and the water, or go a couple of blocks to public transport (monorail to Seattle Center, light rail to/from airport, bus to Museum of Flight).	Only downside is the charge for parking, $27 a night, but that is now standard, if not low, for parking in Seattle.	I don't know when I'll be in Seattle again--it's a long way from Maine!--but when I do I would be happy to stay here again.